X0vtOVAAb4C5bfgax3bj2DVRrCg-hzsv1W1eLDrzHMavEcUFa6KiGrefOKnLV18uiEtsq-YiyKkPfNcmvxsrY8lifVb5PrNZ7ferCYQ9t20q59ULsaXjKzO9h_2zgYzHAzYeUK7I3KX1EZ7oOe-aKjfQwkEEw0AQJaYHtBU3SdozilHHdaXF8fYcQ9oNqlyK5GzM7EbXT4BiFYVkLAlgd-46jqVNG3aedBenViE6SauV7qDtAZHhGfLjlpfr9IZFA-thD_2-n4lo-Go3kSs0ZXJaBlkGc40PwYp2AHEEVg==\",\"summary\":[]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated `X509UtilTest` to make the Bouncy Castle X509 provider implementation classes discoverable before exercising the public APIs that route through `X509Util`.\n\nChanged file:\n\n`tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15on/1.48/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15on/X509UtilTest.java`\n\nWhat changed:\n- Added `makeX509ImplementationsDiscoverableToNativeImage()`.\n- The helper uses constant class names for:\n  - `org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.X509StoreCertCollection`\n  - `org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.X509CertParser`\n- Each test invokes the helper before calling the Bouncy Castle public APIs:\n  - `X509Store.getInstance(...)`\n  - `X509StreamParser.getInstance(...)`\n\nThis keeps the actual dynamic-access target as `org.bouncycastle.x509.X509Util.getImplementation(...)`, while giving Native Image enough static visibility to include the provider implementation classes needed by those dynamic provider mappings.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c5ccc7a2d725f9c016a10b492f73881909d190f9b7ec2a449\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1982, "output": 904, "cacheRead": 69120, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 72006, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779479687269, "responseId": "resp_0c5ccc7a2d725f9c016a10b48812f08190ba998fbe3a9ae67f"}}
